from this keyframe, not from the beginning.

70
00:04:37.133 --> 00:04:40.880
We put a kind of
"checkpoint", a stop at that time,

71
00:04:40.888 --> 00:04:43.793
to make sure that position is fixed.

72
00:04:46.208 --> 00:04:48.705
Now let's see how we flex this.

73
00:04:57.238 --> 00:04:59.642
Here we are going to
have an interpolation

74
00:04:59.642 --> 00:05:03.043
a little weird, we may have to
correct something very subtle,

75
00:05:03.043 --> 00:05:08.060
but there are some slightly
rare deformations in between.

76
00:05:23.010 --> 00:05:26.798
We are going to adjust
these details at the end.

77
00:05:26.888 --> 00:05:30.153
But as long as we can fix
some things, the better.

78
00:05:37.198 --> 00:05:41.912
This is the moment when you
can slow everything down a bit.

79
00:05:50.433 --> 00:05:52.787
And the final moment will be faster.

80
00:05:59.118 --> 00:06:01.445
Now, when the boot starts to take off,

81
00:06:01.445 --> 00:06:05.078
we will adjust the shape

82
00:06:05.078 --> 00:06:07.688
as if it were peeling off the floor.

83
00:06:15.625 --> 00:06:20.433
When making deformations so linked
to another object, such as the floor,

84
00:06:20.433 --> 00:06:23.148
and they are in the middle
of a position transition,

85
00:06:23.148 --> 00:06:26.040
what we can do is
also fix a keyframe there

86
00:06:26.040 --> 00:06:29.163
so that later we can move
those two attributes together,

87
00:06:29.163 --> 00:06:31.527
those of the form and
those of the position.

88
00:06:31.948 --> 00:06:34.108
We can adjust the time a bit,

89
00:06:34.108 --> 00:06:38.365
